track.name: I Can't Get Started
comments: JAZZ CANT GET ANY BETTER THEN THIS OSCAR P AND THE PREZ TWO MELLOW FELLOWS
Very disjointed and not to my taste at all.
true enough Bob...there have other great tenors (i'd hold off on plenty)...but they all owe something to the PRESIDENT...!  rest in peace prez...with your title intact...hahah...!
Plenty of wonderful tenorists out there over the years, but ooh that Prez tone
mr lester young...indisputably the president of tenor sax...no credible challenges to his  title...RIP with much love and appreciation PREZ.
WOW memories of my childhood in new york city!!
Classic Lester. So laid back, with those improvisational touches which make it interesting to listen to.
"I Can't Get Started" is like me in bed on one of those days when I don't want to get up.  And Lester says, "Baby, you don't have to get up.  Just kick it in bed all day."  Thanks, Lester.
